						<summary>

						<p>Slab on the wall of a well in the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1687 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription in Nagari Script records the construction of a <hi rend="italic">dharmasarovara</hi> (tank) and a <hi rend="italic">dharmaśālā</hi> (choultry) by Raṁgōji of Mudgala-gōtra for his own merit.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1609, Prabhava, Chaitra, Śu. 7, Thursday corresponding to 1687 A.D., March 10.</p>						

						</summary>
